data.value: The grade of the plane's tilt (rotation around the length axis)

data.name: DistanceMeasureNode.DisplayScale
data.value: Controls the visual size of the measure node in the viewports

data.name: DistanceMeasureNode.ElevationDelta
data.value: The vertical distance between the start and end points

data.name: DistanceMeasureNode.ShowArrow
data.value: Controls whether to draw the arrow

data.name: DistanceMeasureNode.ShowRing
data.value: Controls whether to draw a ring centered at the start of this measure

data.name: DistanceMeasureNode.ShowText
data.value: Controls whether to display the distance text

data.name: MuckpileSettingsNode.BurdenMode
data.value: Defines where to get per-hole burden values from

data.name: MuckpileSettingsNode.DirectionMode
data.value: Defines where to get per-hole throw direction from. "Explicit" mode uses the per-hole, user defined direction vectors displayed in the face setup tool.

data.name: MuckpileSettingsNode.DrawPerHoleDistances
data.value: Draws a per-hole line that represents the direction and distance of throw

data.name: MuckpileSettingsNode.DrawTerrainFootprint
data.value: When enabled, the terrain projection of the muckpile footprint will be computed. This makes the footprint conform to the terrain but can take some time to compute. The terrain footprint will only draw on top of terrain.

data.name: MuckpileSettingsNode.ApplyRolling
data.value: Controls whether the footprint includes fragment rolling

data.name: MuckpileSettingsNode.A_factor
data.value: Also referred to as the A term from the original paper this model is based on. Higher values generally correspond to harder material causing it to get thrown further.

data.name: MuckpileSettingsNode.Friction
data.value: Controls the rolling friction when rolling is enabled. The higher the friction, the faster fragments will stop rolling.
